Thrilled that @pbskids Talk About: Race & Racism is a 
@DaytimeEmmys
 nominee for outstanding educational & informational series! A as PBS Kids-watcher alumna, it was a treat to host such an important discussion for families. I wrote this poem for kids in the wake of the racial justice protests—here’s to talking to our children about this world that needs what they have to give it.

I’m so proud to finally share this social unity campaign I created, #Vote4theFuture , with @radvocacy 🎉 🎊 . I wrote this poem in a passionate flurry when #RBG passed, and then texted all the leaders in my phone. I was so gratified to get so many yeses from people I admire, and thrilled that my twin sister  @thegabriellegorman came on to direct. Our entire country is raised up when the people come out to the polls. Let’s #Vote4theFuture !
For more info on casting your ballot, visit @whenweallvote @iamavoter @votedotorg @rockthevote @votesaveamerica @2020uptous. 
